{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typepluginprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/type_plugin_ptr-1f7zf"],"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/completeInterfaceInfo(instanceType:interfaceType:info:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/completeTypeInfo(gType:info:valueTable:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/typeAddInterfaceDynamic(instanceType:interfaceType:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/typeRegisterDynamic(parentType:typeName:flags:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/unuse()","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol\/use()"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol"],"title":"Inherited By","kind":"relationships","type":"inheritedBy"},{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginRef"],"title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An interface that handles the lifecycle of dynamically loaded types."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypePluginProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10GLibObject18TypePluginProtocolP","roleHeading":"Protocol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypePluginProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","title":"TypePluginProtocol"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypePluginProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The GObject type system supports dynamic loading of types.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It goes as follows:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The type is initially introduced (usually upon loading the module","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the first time, or by your main application that knows what modules"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"introduces what types), like this:"}]},{"code":["new_type_id = g_type_register_dynamic (parent_type_id,","                                       \"TypeName\",","                                       new_type_plugin,","                                       type_flags);"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"type":"text","text":" is an implementation of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTypePlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" interface."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type’s implementation is referenced, e.g. through"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeClass.ref"},{"type":"text","text":"] or through [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.type_create_instance"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(this is being called by [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.Object.new"},{"text":"]) or through one of the above","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"done on a type derived from ","type":"text"},{"code":"new_type_id","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This causes the type system to load the type’s implementation by calling","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.use","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At some point the type’s implementation isn’t required anymore, e.g. after"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeClass.unref"},{"type":"text","text":"] or [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.type_free_instance"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(called when the reference count of an instance drops to zero).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This causes the type system to throw away the information retrieved"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and then it calls","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.unuse"},{"type":"text","text":"] on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Things may repeat from the second step.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"So basically, you need to implement a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" type that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"carries a use_count, once use_count goes from zero to one, you need","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to load the implementation to successfully handle the upcoming"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] call. Later, maybe after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"succeeding use\/unuse calls, once use_count drops to zero, you can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unload the implementation again. The type system makes sure to call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.use"},{"text":"] and [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"again when the type is needed again."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] is an implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"already implements most of this except for the actual module loading and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unloading. It even handles multiple registered types per module."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GTypePlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypePluginProtocol/unuse()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typepluginprotocol\/unuse()","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"unuse()","abstract":[{"text":"Calls the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unuse_plugin"},{"type":"text","text":" function from the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginClass","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"plugin"},{"type":"text","text":".  There should be no need to use this function outside of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the GObject type system itself."}],"role":"symbol","iden